>The BT878 is the only chipset I know of with DMA audio capture - and which
>nobody uses since they all provide a connector for the sound card instead
Yeah.  I've seen the digital audio port on the Bt878 used, but not for 
actually capturing audio. :-)  You can use it as a general purpose data 
input if you so desire, and it's probably more useful that way for most 
people.
